$ E(X_((1))) = E[P(Y_1 < X_((1)) | X_((1)))] = P(Y_1 < X_((1))) = P(Y_1 < X_1, X_2, .... X_n) = 1/(n+1). $

$ E(X_((1))^2) = E[P(Y_1 < X_((1)); Y_2 < X_((1)) | X_((1)))] = P(Y_1, Y_2 < X_((1))) = P(Y_1, Y_2 < X_1, X_2, .... X_n) = 1/C_(n+2)^2. $


